snippet.textDisplay: New challenge idea: this is something we like to do from time to time. We go out and buy several frozen food items, and with things in our pantry we try to make the better and the best we can. Either by combining frozen foods together, adding ingredients, different cooking preps, etc. It's a fun game. Sometimes it's amazing what you can do to a $5 frozen pizza...and other times it doesn't work out no matter what you try ha.

snippet.textDisplay: Mum used to put Vegemite in her Bolognese sauce so I was totally on-board with the marmite. Turns out half of my family is quite intolerant to yeast extract though (yeast is fine) so she doesn't do that anymore. I've had to learn to live without strong umami flavours as I can't tolerate yeast extract, MSG or any of its friends (free glutamates) or flavour enhancers.

snippet.textDisplay: A different perspective. All you guys had to do was stir, sure.  But that's what he would have been doing too.  As Ben said, you guys didn't come up with sides or garnishes...and Jamie didn't even do the stirring part. don't worry about a process you don't have "control" over...sometimes the best thing to do is keep the process going.  Find things to add...you guys have been doing this for over 10 years and don't know what goes with the stuff you're making? You haven't thought about sides for dishes?  What flavors accompany the main dishes that you've made in the past?  You all have come a long way...the fact that you didn't screw up the risotto is LITERALLY steps above where y'all were starting this show out.  If you want to have agency in the recipies you make...maybe learn to branch out a bit?  Besides...y'all are great people and just need to keep learning.  That said...maybe it's time to do a few episodes on how to make sides to go with a meal?
